The paper deals with graph partitioning problems, which are often studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The problem of finding a partition with certain degree constraints can also be seen as a constraint satisfaction problem, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the problem involves analyzing the minimum degree of graphs, which is a fundamental concept in graph theory and can be studied in the area of computational geometry (cs.CG) as well. Finally, the paper uses techniques from algorithm design and analysis, which are relevant to the area of data structures (cs.DS).
